Package: trafficr
Title: Traffic Assignment Methods
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Douglas", "Martins", email="douglas.capelossi@gmail.com", role=c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Douglas Martins [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Douglas Martins <douglas.capelossi@gmail.com>
Description: R package for obtaining the user equilibrium solution with Frank-Wolfe Algorithm in urban traffic assignment, 
	heavily based on 'dodgr' package for all-or-nothing assignment, route and time data.
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)
Imports: dplyr,tidyr,data.table,sf,sp,dodgr (== 0.2.0),stringi,readr,tmap,matrixcalc,callr, digest, igraph, magrittr, methods,
		osmdata, rbenchmark,Rcpp (>= 0.12.6), RcppParallel
Suggests: ggplot2, igraphdata, jsonlite, knitr, purrr,
        RColorBrewer, rmarkdown, roxygen2, scales, tidygraph
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.0.2
URL: http://github.com/douglascm/trafficr
BugReports: http://github.com/douglascm/trafficr
